[normal] 
[normal]In total, 
[normal]65.5 per cent of respondents said they thought th
[normal]ese standards were either satisfactory or too high (with only 5.6 per cent saying they were too low)
[normal]. 
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Effect of [bold]Registration Scheme and Register Competition[bold]5.1[bold] 
[normal]The survey asked: Which of the statements about the competition between CPS 
[normal]providers
[normal] do you a
[normal]gree with:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.2[bold] 
[normal]Responses indicate that all of these factors 
[normal]play a part
[normal] in the current 
[normal]electrical Competent Person Scheme arena
[normal]. A total of 20.4 per cent thought competition was bad because it drove standards down and 28.2 per cent thought it was bad because it limited c
[normal]onsumer awareness. However, this is set against the 38.2 per cent of respondents who thought that competition was good because without it prices would be higher and the 59.6 per cent that thought competition was good because it 
[normal]offered
[normal] them choice.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.3[bold] 
[normal]By
[normal] recoding
[normal] this data into positive and negative statements, we can see that while 48.6 per cent of respondents thought competition was bad, more than twice as many (97.8) saw competition as a good thing for them.
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.4[bold] 
[normal]The two negative aspects of competiti
[normal]on that we have identified here are currently being addressed 
[normal]in line with
[normal] DCLG
[normal]’s 2012
[normal] Conditions of 
[normal]A
[normal]uthorisation
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.5[bold] 
[normal]It is hoped that the new EAS 2012 standards,
[normal] to be
[normal] introduced in June 2014, will help to address the current issues in the industry
[normal] aro
[normal]und the dilution of standards
[normal]. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.6[bold] 
[normal]T
[normal]he concern that competition creates a confused market for consumers
[normal] has also been addressed. 
[normal]One of 
[normal]DCLG
[normal]’s 
[normal]Conditions of Authorisation is
[normal] to
[normal] promote awareness of the Competent Person Scheme to consumers.
[normal] 
[normal]This response highlights 
[normal]the effec
[normal]ts of competition in the market
[normal] going forward, will be 
[normal]predominantly
[normal] 
[normal]positive.
